** API Keys 
https://aider.chat/docs/config/api-keys.html
Aider lets you specify API keys in a few ways:

,* On the command line
,* As environment variables
,* In a .env file
,* In your .aider.conf.yml config file
** models
Aider works best with Claude 3.5 Sonnet, DeepSeek R1 & Chat V3,
OpenAI o1, o3-mini & GPT-4o. Aider can [[https://aider.chat/docs/llms.html][connect to almost any LLM,
including local models]].

# o3-mini
$ aider --model o3-mini --api-key openai=<key>

# Claude 3.7 Sonnet
$ aider --model sonnet --api-key anthropic=<key>

Or you can run aider --model XXX to launch aider with another
model. During your chat you can switch models with the in-chat
/model command.

